Title: Fine-tuning and the Wilson renormalization group
Authors: M. Bonini and E. Tricarico
Comments: 21 pages, Latex epsfig to be published in Nucl.Phys.B
Report-no: UPRF-00-04
Journal-ref: Nucl.Phys. B585 (2000) 253-274
\\
  We use the Wilson renormalization group (RG) formulation to solve the
fine-tuning procedure needed in renormalization schemes breaking the gauge
symmetry. To illustrate this method we systematically compute the non-invariant
couplings of the ultraviolet action of the SU(2) pure Yang-Mills theory at
one-loop order.
